My apologies for the confusion earlier. Here's the corrected implementation with additional challenging unit tests using the `@test` macro:

```julia
using Test

abstract type AbstractVehicle end

struct Car <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Motorcycle <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Bus <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Truck <: AbstractVehicle end

ispersonal(v::AbstractVehicle) = v isa Car || v isa Motorcycle

@testset begin
    @test ispersonal(Car()) == true
    @test ispersonal(Motorcycle()) == true
    @test ispersonal(Bus()) == false
    @test ispersonal(Truck()) == false
    @test ispersonal(Any()) == false
end
```

Apologies for the oversight. Let's update the unit test to pass. The `Any` type does not represent a concrete subtype of `AbstractVehicle`. Here's the corrected implementation and unit tests:

